<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-600-702  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 600 702.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>MacWEEK  August 15 1989 v3 n30 p20(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT MacWEEK Inc. 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>RetixMail compatible with X.400 standard. (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Said, Carolyn.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Retix (product introduction).andO;Product:   RetixMail for Macintosh (Electronic mail system) (productintroduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionX.400 ProtocolCompatible SoftwareTelecommunicationsElectronic Mail Systems.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>By Carolyn SaidandM;Santa Monica, Calif.andP;  -- Promising to make global electronic mail a realityfor the Macintosh before the year is out, telecommunications developer Retixhas announced the first Mac mail system that is compatible with theinternational X.400 standard.andM;RetixMail for Macintosh will ship in November, the company said.andP;  It will befully compatible with X.400, a messaging standard established by theConsultative Committee on International Telephone and Telegraph (CCITT) andincorporated into OSI (open systems interconnect) protocols for linkingmixed-platform environments.andM;&quot;The beauty of X.400 is that addressing, routing and other datacommunications issues are transparent,&quot; said David Knight, RetixMail productmanager.andP;  &quot;With RetixMail for Macintosh you can send a message or file fromyour Mac to 50 people worldwide on a variety of systems just as easily as youcan to someone sitting near you on [an IBM] PC or a [Digital Equipment Corp.]andO;VAX.&quot;andM;Retix kicked off its X.400 product line last fall with a PC version ofRetixMail.andM;RetixMail for Macintosh must run on a mixed-platform LAN that supports acommon file server for Macs and PCs, such as Novell's NetWare, Dayna'sDaynaNET, Banyan Systems' VINES, 3Com's 3+ or TOPS.andP;  RetixMail users share acommon Retix OpenServer 400 Message Server, operating on a PC or compatible.andM;RetixMail for Macintosh will be available in a 100-user package that includesOpenServer 400 for $7,300.andM;Retix is located at 2644 30th St., Santa Monica, Calif.andP;  90405; (213)399-2200.andP;  n</TEXT></DOC>